Hereâ€™s a list of the commands you'll need to set a user icon in Rocky Linux with XFCE:

1. Navigate to the folder where the image is stored:
$ cd ~/Downloads

2. Copy the image to the correct folder (icons directory):
$ sudo cp Tyler.jpg /var/lib/AccountsService/icons/agn3y

3. Create or edit the user configuration file:
$ sudo vi /var/lib/AccountsService/users/agn3y

4. Add the following content to the file (replace agn3y with your username):
Icon=/var/lib/AccountsService/icons/Tyler.jpg

5. Then save changes and Reboot:
$ sudo reboot

